thread.title_full: Top 10 Comments of the Week: adidas, Kanye West, Supreme & More

author: Brian Farmer
title: Top 10 Comments of the Week: adidas, Kanye West, Supreme & More
text:
This past week Supreme released branded MetroCards at select stations throughout NYC, NASA discovered 7 Earth-sized planets orbiting a nearby star, we showed you what adidas Boost headphones might look like, and Kanye West announced that he’ll be launching his own makeup brand.
Below you’ll find a roundup of our favorite comments from the week, spanning the aforementioned posts and a few others. Please be sure to keep the funny, interesting and bizarre comments coming, and in the meantime check out this week’s finest below.
Please keep in mind these comments are meant to be taken as jokes and are only highlighted for the comedic effect they offer. 
#10 commented on: Designers Use Apple Products to Imagine What the iCar Will Look Like 
“Looks like the vhs cars that would rewind your vhs”
Miguel Mendez #09 commented on: Here’s a First Look at the Public School x Air Jordan 12 Wheat 
“NYC Timberlands digivolving”
Robin Hedin #08 commented on: Supreme MetroCards Are Causing Chaos At NYC Subway Stations 
“Y’all dumb motherfuckers would break your own legs if Supreme released a wheelchair.”
Oppiken #07 commented on: Here’s a Second Round of Street Style From Copenhagen Fashion Week FW17 
“When you’re homeless but gotta be at a show at 12”
Chris Spitz #06 commented on: Supreme MetroCards Are Causing Chaos At NYC Subway Stations 
“Taking L’s on the way to work has never been so easy”
Taylor Scriber #05 commented on: NASA Discovers 7 Earth-Size Planets Orbiting Nearby Star 
“Kyrie said the earth is flat… these flat too?”
Beau John Mair #04 commented on: Sriracha Changes the Game Again With New Seasoning Stix 
“I heard they work on a colab with Supreme. Sriracha x Supreme. Lit af.”
Julius J. Diekmeyer #03 commented on: Here’s What a Set of adidas Boost Headphones Might Look Like 
“Boost everything. Shit so comfortable. Boost my car seats, boost my couch, boost my hat.”
Greg Hoffmann #02 commented on: This Supreme-Decaled Porsche 911 Is Every Streetwear Kid’s Dream 
“You could put the Supreme logo on a Nissan Cube and hypebeasts will say they love the silhouette”
James Cudahy #01 commented on: Kanye West Is Launching a Makeup Brand 
“Dear slim i wrote you but you still ain’t callin I left my cell my pager and my home phone at the bottom”
Mishka Ninikashvili
